[[Image:Fourtops-reachout-album.jpg|thumb|250px|right|The Four Tops' ''[[Reach Out (album)|Reach Out]]'' was released in 1966 and became one of their highest-charted albums during their tenure in [[Motown Records|Motown]] reaching number eleven on the [[Billboard Top 200|US Pop Singles chart]]. The album featured the group's last collaborations with [[Holland-Dozier-Holland]], who parted a year after the release of this album.]]

This is a listing of all the singles and albums released by legendary [[Motown Records|Motown]] singing group [[The Four Tops]]. Throughout their career, twenty-four of their singles reached the [[Billboard Hot 100|Billboard Top 40]] with seven of them reaching the top ten and two of them reaching #1 on the chart. An additional twenty-one have reached the [[UK Top 75|UK Top 40]] with ten reaching the top ten and one reaching #1 on the chart.
